$$\displaystyle \begin{aligned} k_{1,2}^{Y}\,\propto \, \mathrm{exp}(-\frac{E_a}{k_B\,T}) \quad  \Longrightarrow \quad  \frac{\tau_{1,2}^Y(T_0)}{\tau_{1,2}^Y(T_1)}\,=\,\frac{k_{1,2}^Y(T_1)}{k_{1,2}^Y(T_0)}\,=\,\mathrm{exp} \bigl[\frac{E_a}{k_B}\,(\frac{1}{T_0}-\frac{1}{T_1}) \bigr], {} \end{aligned} $$
\end{document} where Ea is the energy required for defect dissociation or formation.

