As already mentioned the defects in the semiconductor lattice give rise to energy levels (states) in the band gap affecting the operation of semiconductor detector mainly in three ways as shown in Fig. 21.5. 
Some of the defects can be charged which leads to (Chap. 5) (Fig. 21.5a) changes in the electric field. For semiconductor detectors this may result in loss of the depleted (active) region requiring an increase of the applied bias. The bias voltage is however limited by the device break down. The space charge is calculated as a difference in concentration of charged donors and charged acceptors, 21.14Neff=∑donorsNt(1−Pt)−∑acceptorsNtPt,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
